text:
Who said that? Regading what?


…this innovation will create forgetfulness in the learners’ souls, because they will not use their memories;
it gives not truth, but only the appearance of truth;
the students will be hearers of many things and will have learned nothing;
they will appear to be omniscient and will generally know nothing, having the show of wisdom without the reality.



Socrates, 5th century BCE, about WRITING
